title: LES MILLS | Choose Happy with Brett Goldstein
description:
Choose a workout you actually enjoy with Les Mills. 

Watch as Brett Goldstein makes his way through fitness hell to find a workout from one of the happiest places on earth, New Zealand. 

â€œChoose Happyâ€ is our new international campaign aimed at helping the 64 percent of Gen Z who aren't regularly exercising to overcome barriers such as intimidation and reap the rewards of an active lifestyle. 

We have partnered with breakthrough creative force Brett Goldstein â€” naming him the first Les Mills Happiness Ambassador â€” to show that when you choose a workout you enjoy, you work out harder and happier.

To succeed Brett, weâ€™re also announcing a unique competition for two fitness fans to win a dream move to New Zealand for three months and become Goldsteinâ€™s successors as the next two Happiness Ambassadors. Applicants simply need to visit www.lesmills.com/choosehappy and explain why they should be chosen, with the winners announced via the Les Mills social media accounts on 29th July NZT during LES MILLS LIVE Los Angeles.

Each Ambassador will receive an adventure filled happy itinerary to the value of $40,000 NZD, so that they can master the art of happiness. Following in the footsteps of Goldstein, the Happiness Ambassadors will be welcomed into the Les Mills family for the full Kiwi experience, training with the brandâ€™s world-leading instructors and receiving a personal tour from its founder Phillip Mills, taking in some of New Zealandâ€™s most breathtaking landmarks. 

#LesMills #ChooseHappy #NewZealand #BrettGoldstein
____

Les Mills is the global leader in group fitness and creator of over 25 programs available in leading fitness facilities around the world. Les Mills programs include the worldâ€™s first group exercise resistance training workout BODYPUMPâ„¢, BODYCOMBATâ„¢ (martial arts), RPMâ„¢ (indoor cycling), BODYBALANCEâ„¢ (yoga), LES MILLS GRITâ„¢ (30-minute high-intensity interval training) and the revolutionary immersive cycle experience, THE TRIPâ„¢. Each workout is refreshed and updated with new choreography and music every three months.

The company was founded by Les Mills â€” a four-time Olympian and head coach of New Zealandâ€™s track and field team â€” who opened his first gym in 1968 with the aim of taking elite sports training to the masses. Today, Les Mills workouts are delivered by 130,000 certified instructors in 21,000 clubs across 100 countries, as well as via the LES MILLS+ streaming platform and Virtual Reality (VR).

Dr Jackie Mills, M.D. and Diana Archer Mills explain the benefits of BODYBALANCE, and come back on how, for the past 50 years, Les Mills has transformed the way we practice yoga to what we now call New Generation Yoga. 

In 1997, BODYBALANCE was born: a series of simple yoga moves, elements of Tai Chi and Pilates with an inspiring soundtrack in the background. Breathing control is a part of all the exercises, and instructors will always provide options for those just getting started.

title: LES MILLS TECHNIQUE | How to Safely Do A Squat?
description:
Learn how to safely do squats with Corey Baird, Les Mills Technical Consultant.

You can find a class here: https://www.lesmills.com/findaclass
Or work out via LES MILLS On Demand: https://www.lesmills.com/ondemand/workouts/strength-training/

Sign-up to a LES MILLS On Demand free trial here: https://lmod.co/onlineworkouts

How to do the perfect squat?
1. Place your feet slightly wider than your hips
2. Position your feet with toe angled 5-20 degrees outward
3. Lift your chest
4. Ensure your weight is distributed through the heels and balls of your feet
5. Brace your core muscles.

The movement
1. Push your hips back and keep pushing them back as the knees begin to bend
2. Ensure your knees track forward in line with the middle of each foot
3. Keep your chest lifted
4. Squat down until your knees are at 90 degrees
5. Drive through your heels to return to standing
6. Keep the core tight throughout the movement.

title: LES MILLS TECHNIQUE | How To Safely Do A Burpee?
description:
Learn how to safely do burpees with Corey Baird, Les Mills Technical Consultant.

If you like the idea of smashing out sets of burpees, give LES MILLS GRIT a go. They are also a regular feature in BODYATTACK and BODYSTEP.

You can find a class here: https://www.lesmills.com/findaclass
Or work out via LES MILLS On Demand: https://www.lesmills.com/ondemand/workouts/cardio/

Sign-up to a LES MILLS On Demand free trial here: https://lmod.co/onlineworkouts

Burpees are a fast way to shift your fitness to another level. They are great for improving cardio endurance, torching your fat and burning calories. Burpees take your heart rate up, they strengthen your legs, your core muscles and your upper body.

The burpee technique:
1. When you squat, make sure your feet are slightly wider than the hips to keep your chest upright
2. Feet are angled out 5 to 20 degrees to allow your abs to support your lower back
3. Bend the legs to land to absorb the load
